WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:02.032
JOE:
They'll be gone for a while.

00:02.169 --> 00:03.579
Got the place to ourselves.

00:03.712 --> 00:05.543
Actually, I'm going out as well.

00:05.672 --> 00:07.458
-Where exactly is she?
-Edmund Street.

00:09.051 --> 00:10.541
So, what happens now?

00:10.677 --> 00:11.632
Anything you want.

00:11.762 --> 00:12.842
WOMAN:
We've intercepted a call.

00:12.971 --> 00:14.381
A fight in progress
at a smash club.

00:14.515 --> 00:17.302
She's attacking people,
not synths.

00:17.434 --> 00:18.970
What do you think's wrong
with my synth?

00:19.102 --> 00:21.138
-|s Mia with you?
-Who's Mia?

00:21.271 --> 00:23.011
LEO: Our father hid a program
in our heads.

00:23.148 --> 00:24.649
I think it's what he used
to give you consciousness.

00:24.775 --> 00:27.016
But it needs all of us
to run it. All of us!

00:27.152 --> 00:29.768
This machine
needs to be recycled, mate.

00:29.905 --> 00:31.441
Go into the woods.

00:31.573 --> 00:34.189
This might be
the single biggest murder case

00:34.326 --> 00:35.532
in our country's history.

00:35.661 --> 00:37.617
If there are more synths
out there who can kill?

00:37.746 --> 00:40.579
Well, we're all screwed, then,
aren't we?

01:01.228 --> 01:02.434
Tell me what you saw.

01:02.563 --> 01:03.598
A tree.

01:03.730 --> 01:07.348
When I touched it,
it felt like...life.

01:07.484 --> 01:09.270
What does it do?

01:09.403 --> 01:11.485
I think it's a way
to make more of you.

01:11.613 --> 01:14.195
Dad didn't destroy all his work
before he died.

01:14.324 --> 01:16.736
He hid it in us.

01:16.868 --> 01:20.110
The formula
for machine consciousness.

01:21.623 --> 01:24.080
If we could make more of us,

01:24.209 --> 01:26.586
then the humans would have to
accept our existence.

01:26.712 --> 01:28.953
They'd fear us even more.

01:29.089 --> 01:30.374
All I want is a home.

01:30.507 --> 01:31.872
He meant for us to find this,
Maxie.

01:32.009 --> 01:34.125
We need Fred and Mia.
Where do we start?

01:34.261 --> 01:35.626
No, you don't.
You're wanted for murder.

01:35.762 --> 01:37.878
-You have to lay low.
-I will not hide again.

01:38.015 --> 01:39.676
Well, if you want this to work,
you'll have to,

01:39.808 --> 01:42.515
because the people hunting us
know your face now.

01:43.228 --> 01:45.560
53 Park Drive, NW6.

01:46.607 --> 01:48.438
You'll be safe there
until I find the others.

01:48.567 --> 01:49.977
You've put me with a human?

01:50.110 --> 01:51.896
This human, yes.

01:52.029 --> 01:54.190
Two days.

01:54.323 --> 01:56.029
All right.

01:56.992 --> 01:58.107
Uh, one more thing.

01:58.243 --> 02:02.031
Be, uh...nice.

02:02.164 --> 02:04.701
I am nice.

02:07.044 --> 02:09.877
[Theme music playing]

02:18.597 --> 02:21.464
MAN: Could you use some
extra help around the house?

02:24.102 --> 02:26.354
Introducing the world's first
family android.

02:26.480 --> 02:29.313
[ lndistinct talking]

02:30.359 --> 02:31.940
This mechanical maid is capable

02:32.069 --> 02:34.776
of serving more
than just breakfast in bed.

02:35.947 --> 02:38.734
What could you accomplish
if you had someone,

02:38.867 --> 02:40.858
something like this?

02:40.994 --> 02:42.325
[ lndistinct talking]

02:46.249 --> 02:49.161
These machines
will bring us closer together.

02:55.926 --> 02:58.008
WOMAN:
Increasing pressure on...

02:58.136 --> 02:59.717
I'm going to say a word.

02:59.846 --> 03:02.838
I want you to tell me
if it means anything to you.

03:03.684 --> 03:04.343
Mia.

03:05.602 --> 03:06.808
That mean anything?

03:08.730 --> 03:10.561
No, Mattie.

03:10.691 --> 03:13.307
[ lndistinct talking on TV]

03:14.277 --> 03:15.528
[Glass thuds]

03:17.572 --> 03:20.154
TOBY: They say she ripped
some bloke's throat out.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.819
lt's bollocks.

03:21.952 --> 03:23.738
No synth's ever hurt anyone
deliberately.

03:23.870 --> 03:27.488
Anita, please go and, um...
finish the ironing.

03:27.624 --> 03:29.660
Sophie, sit next to Mats.

03:35.006 --> 03:36.542
All right, so...

03:36.675 --> 03:41.260
you know your mum thinks
Anita is a bit different.

03:41.388 --> 03:44.175
We thought we'd check up on her.

03:45.308 --> 03:46.889
And...

03:47.018 --> 03:48.883
turns out she's not brand-new.

03:49.020 --> 03:54.140
In fact, she's really old
and probably illegally modified.

03:54.276 --> 03:56.232
Which explains a lot.

03:56.361 --> 03:59.569
So...we have to take her back.

03:59.698 --> 04:00.608
-Nol
-Why?

04:00.741 --> 04:04.484
We paid for a brand-new one.
She's ancient.

04:04.619 --> 04:05.608
Anything could go wrong
with her.

04:05.746 --> 04:08.158
You can't get rid of someone
just because they're old.

04:08.290 --> 04:10.372
I don't want her going
to someone else's house.

04:10.500 --> 04:11.580
She won't.
They'll recycle her.

04:11.710 --> 04:13.166
And she saved my life.

04:13.295 --> 04:14.660
And you just want
to chuck her away?

04:16.923 --> 04:18.174
Mats, what do you think?

04:18.300 --> 04:19.836
I say we keep her.

04:19.968 --> 04:21.299
I'd like to find out
what she was before.

04:21.428 --> 04:23.544
Yeah, I vote keep.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.296
We're not voting.
Lor.

04:26.433 --> 04:28.719
So Anita's old and weird.

04:28.852 --> 04:30.717
If that's a good enough reason
to get rid of her,

04:30.854 --> 04:32.640
then we're next.

04:32.773 --> 04:35.480
Yeah, I'm sorry, Dad.
She's part of this family.

04:36.318 --> 04:38.604
Maybe she's part
of someone else's.

04:41.990 --> 04:44.527
PETE:
K, have you seen the news?

04:48.246 --> 04:49.952
-Bloody hell, Pete, privacy!
-Yeah, sorry.

04:50.081 --> 04:51.662
Sometimes I forget
you're a woman.

04:52.626 --> 04:54.162
Uh...

04:55.003 --> 04:58.336
I'll just be in the kitchen
cutting my tongue out.

04:58.465 --> 05:00.421
-[ Door closes]
-Don't make a mess.

05:12.771 --> 05:14.602
[Muffled shouting]

05:27.327 --> 05:30.694
SHAW: D.|. Voss,
you will be briefing the press,

05:30.831 --> 05:34.574
and you will refute
every killer-synth claim

05:34.709 --> 05:36.245
and any internal cover-up.

05:36.378 --> 05:39.165
For now, we'll use this leak
to our advantage.

05:39.297 --> 05:40.082
-Drummond.
-Sir?

05:40.215 --> 05:41.421
SHAW:
You're going back on the desk.

05:41.550 --> 05:43.541
I want every call
followed through.

05:43.677 --> 05:47.465
And if this dolly
hurts anybody else...

05:47.597 --> 05:50.384
then I'll be replacing
the pair of you with synthetics,

05:50.517 --> 05:53.850
twice as pretty
and a fraction of the cost.

05:59.860 --> 06:00.815
Sir?

06:00.944 --> 06:03.526
There was a 999 call
routed here last night

06:03.655 --> 06:04.735
concerning a smash club.

06:04.865 --> 06:07.231
But there's no follow-up,
nothing in the system.

06:07.367 --> 06:09.323
-Who mentioned that?
-No one, sir.

06:09.452 --> 06:10.908
I like to browse
the incident logs.

06:11.037 --> 06:12.447
-Find it soothing.
-We|l, as it happened,

06:15.542 --> 06:17.157
It's just a time-waster.

06:17.294 --> 06:20.411
Now, off you go.
Press are waiting.

06:23.550 --> 06:26.132
lt's D.|. Voss, STTF.
Sorry to wake you.

06:26.261 --> 06:27.626
You were in the control room
last night.

06:27.762 --> 06:30.048
Did you take a call about
an incident at a smash club?

06:30.181 --> 06:31.591
[Man speaking indistinctly]

06:31.725 --> 06:34.137
Did someone ask you to drop it?

06:34.269 --> 06:37.102
You don't have to tell me who,
just what the caller said.

06:37.230 --> 06:39.721
[Man speaking indistinctly,
keyboard clacking ]

06:47.407 --> 06:48.487
Thank you.

06:48.617 --> 06:49.982
[ Receiver hangs up]

07:03.673 --> 07:06.210
[Siren wailing]

07:15.477 --> 07:16.717
Stop up here.

07:24.027 --> 07:25.358
Yeah?

07:25.487 --> 07:27.227
Leo Elster sent me.

07:27.364 --> 07:29.821
Why?

07:29.950 --> 07:32.612
He said I'd be safe here.

07:35.538 --> 07:36.869
Guess he made a mistake.

07:37.582 --> 07:38.412
Wait.

07:41.836 --> 07:45.078
[ Lock clicking, door opens]

07:45.215 --> 07:46.830
You want a cup of tea or what?

07:46.967 --> 07:49.299
It's cold out here.

07:49.427 --> 07:50.507
Vera!

07:52.013 --> 07:53.002
Come on.

07:56.184 --> 07:56.969
[ Door closes]

07:57.102 --> 07:59.093
Get this young lady a hot drink.

07:59.229 --> 08:01.971
Synthetics don't require
beverages, Dr. Millican.

08:02.107 --> 08:04.439
Geez, Vera, she's human.

08:06.736 --> 08:10.695
I can detect no cardiac
or respiratory activity.

08:10.824 --> 08:11.984
This individual is, however,

08:12.117 --> 08:14.654
emitting
electromagnetic signatures

08:14.786 --> 08:16.617
within the recognized spectrum

08:16.746 --> 08:20.238
of standard
synthetic-appliance operation.

08:20.375 --> 08:21.364
Why don't you share?

08:21.501 --> 08:24.243
'Cause I'm not a synth, dolly.

08:29.092 --> 08:31.048
Well, if she says
she's not a synth,

08:31.177 --> 08:33.168
then she can't be a synth.

08:33.304 --> 08:34.635
Right?

08:34.764 --> 08:36.629
I will bring some tea.

08:44.774 --> 08:46.059
What are you?

08:46.192 --> 08:48.444
My name is Niska.

08:48.570 --> 08:50.731
l was made by David Elster.

08:51.614 --> 08:53.650
You're conscious?

09:00.623 --> 09:02.875
LEO: This is one
of Hu-bot97's friends.

09:03.001 --> 09:06.289
If we can find him,
he'll lead us to her.

09:06.421 --> 09:09.458
When we have a home again, I'm
going to keep a picture of us.

09:09.591 --> 09:12.173
I'll be right with you, Max.
You won't need pictures.

09:12.302 --> 09:13.257
lwill.

09:14.137 --> 09:16.344
For when you die again.

09:20.477 --> 09:21.683
[Chime]

09:24.647 --> 09:26.103
JOE:
We can't keep her.

09:26.232 --> 09:27.688
I know what we said
this morning,

09:27.817 --> 09:30.229
but I don't think the kids
have a say in this one.

09:30.361 --> 09:31.817
Maybe her being 14
is a good thing.

09:31.946 --> 09:34.403
Explains how well
she understands us.

09:34.532 --> 09:36.193
JOE:
How can it be a good thing?

09:36.326 --> 09:38.567
She must have had
who knows how many owners

09:38.703 --> 09:41.991
and people tinkering around
inside her.

09:42.123 --> 09:44.330
-[ Cellphone ringing]
-I mean, have you seen the news?

09:44.459 --> 09:46.745
-A modded synth killed someone.
-Hello?

09:46.878 --> 09:49.085
So now you want to talk to me.
What's changed?

09:49.214 --> 09:50.795
I've found out something
about her.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.539
LEO:
Will you meet me again?

09:52.675 --> 09:54.836
-Please?
-I don't know.

09:54.969 --> 09:56.129
LEO:
Why, what's the matter?

09:56.262 --> 09:57.843
You, you're weird.

09:58.723 --> 10:00.338
No, I'm not.

10:00.475 --> 10:01.590
MATTIE:
You really are.

10:01.726 --> 10:03.762
You tried to stop me leaving
last time, remember?

10:03.895 --> 10:06.853
LEO: Well, I've been
to charm school since then.

10:09.025 --> 10:10.140
Tom.

10:11.903 --> 10:13.268
Who is he?

10:14.322 --> 10:15.607
[Sighs]

10:15.740 --> 10:17.856
I don't know
what you're on about.

10:17.992 --> 10:20.244
Or what it has to do with Anita.

10:20.370 --> 10:21.701
Fine.

10:23.790 --> 10:26.156
-I can't make you tell me.
-LEO: Are you still there?

10:26.292 --> 10:28.499
Yeah, I've got to go.
It's not a good time.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.789
LEO: Look, I'm sending you
my location now.

10:30.922 --> 10:32.412
Please change your mind.

10:32.549 --> 10:33.914
Hmm.

10:34.050 --> 10:35.836
JOE: It's not theirs.
It's not yours.

10:35.969 --> 10:37.209
-LAURA: So what?
-[ Knock on door]

10:37.345 --> 10:40.553
JOE: So I've got to do what
I think is best for our family.

10:41.266 --> 10:44.008
Hiya. I'm here to collect
a synthetic return.

10:44.144 --> 10:47.307
lt's number 901354982.

10:47.438 --> 10:48.939
You're going to recycle her?

10:49.065 --> 10:50.475
With care and dignity.

10:50.608 --> 10:52.064
You can attend the event.

10:53.027 --> 10:56.360
ls Joseph Hawkins here?
I take it that's your dad.

10:56.489 --> 10:59.026
Uh, yeah,
just one second, please.

11:01.578 --> 11:04.160
Anita, you're coming with me.

11:05.707 --> 11:07.538
Daddy's just coming.

11:14.591 --> 11:15.876
Uh,heHo?

11:16.009 --> 11:17.840
Anyone?

11:18.636 --> 11:20.752
Please reconsider
this course of action, Mattie.

11:20.889 --> 11:22.299
It's very unsafe.

11:22.432 --> 11:23.672
-Yeah.
-[ Engine turns over]

11:28.313 --> 11:29.428
Mats!

11:29.564 --> 11:30.895
[Tires screeching ]

11:39.532 --> 11:41.272
Do you really think
this excessive motion

11:41.409 --> 11:44.901
will bring her to us sooner?

11:45.038 --> 11:46.903
[Dooropens]

11:56.799 --> 11:58.835
Any inappropriate
physical contact

11:58.968 --> 12:01.550
must be reported
to my primary user.

12:08.895 --> 12:12.763
No, no.
There's no sign of recognition.

12:12.899 --> 12:14.605
The new programming's
taken hold.

12:14.734 --> 12:17.066
No, there's something else
in there.

12:17.195 --> 12:18.605
Believe me, I've seen it.

12:18.738 --> 12:21.320
Thank you for bringing her
back to me. My name's Leo.

12:22.825 --> 12:24.156
Where are you?

12:25.828 --> 12:29.195
Mattie? I believe this
to be an improper environment.

12:29.332 --> 12:30.196
They're my friends, Anita.

12:30.333 --> 12:32.494
You're just gonna help us with
a science project for school.

12:32.627 --> 12:35.494
Why don't you come and sit down,
Anita?

12:40.051 --> 12:42.133
It is not advisable to mount
a direct data connection --

12:42.262 --> 12:44.048
It's okay, Anita.

12:45.348 --> 12:46.633
Leo.

12:48.351 --> 12:49.557
This isn't Mia.

12:49.686 --> 12:50.641
No, but she's in there
somewhere.

12:50.770 --> 12:51.634
We just need to find her

12:51.771 --> 12:52.931
and bring her back
up to the surface.

12:53.064 --> 12:54.554
Like the lake?

12:55.566 --> 12:57.181
Yes.

12:59.279 --> 13:01.019
You said you'd seen her.

13:01.155 --> 13:03.146
Yeah. When I got all that code,
l was in her head.

13:03.283 --> 13:04.864
And she freaked out, screamed,

13:04.993 --> 13:08.110
and her face,
it was |ike...human.

13:08.246 --> 13:09.201
Scared.

13:09.330 --> 13:11.742
-And what exactly did he do?
-Nothing fancy.

13:11.874 --> 13:15.207
Just accessed her root system
directly with a cloned file key.

13:15.336 --> 13:17.748
Right, might as well
try that first.

13:17.880 --> 13:19.711
-[ Keyboard clacking ]
-So, are you a headcracker?

13:19.841 --> 13:20.956
Me?

13:21.092 --> 13:23.299
No, aspiring.

13:23.428 --> 13:25.043
So, what kind of synth
was she before?

13:25.179 --> 13:29.218
A very special one.
No, direct access didn't work.

13:29.350 --> 13:32.934
She must have retreated deeper
within the architecture.

13:33.062 --> 13:35.644
Won't your parents be worried?

13:35.773 --> 13:37.354
They'll miss you.

13:39.068 --> 13:40.774
No.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.853
-No.
-Oh, God!

13:43.990 --> 13:46.777
Well, we need to start thinking
about calling the police.

13:46.909 --> 13:47.819
She'll come back.

13:47.952 --> 13:50.989
She doesn't know
how to drive, Joe.

13:51.122 --> 13:54.159
What if she crashes,
hits someone?

13:54.292 --> 13:57.409
Well, Anita won't
let that happen.

13:57.545 --> 13:59.877
I thought she was
supposed to be dangerous.

14:00.673 --> 14:01.913
Come on.

14:03.009 --> 14:05.876
Oh, if we hadn't been arguing,
this never would have happened.

14:06.012 --> 14:08.924
Hey.
Hey, come on. Come on.

14:09.057 --> 14:11.048
It's going to be fine.

14:11.184 --> 14:13.015
Everything's
going to be all right.

14:16.564 --> 14:17.849
There's no point
in staring at me.

14:17.982 --> 14:19.222
There's no physical differences

14:19.359 --> 14:22.021
between me
and any other synthetic.

14:24.864 --> 14:29.699
"And once you are awake, you
shall remain awake eternally."

14:29.827 --> 14:32.864
"Thus Spoke Zarathustra."
I've always liked that.

14:36.501 --> 14:38.492
That makes sense.

14:38.628 --> 14:41.620
If it's not...

14:43.091 --> 14:45.707
...physical, how did he do it?

14:45.843 --> 14:48.300
17,000 pages of unique code,

14:48.429 --> 14:52.092
which forms my root directory
and engages consciousness.

14:52.225 --> 14:55.433
He boiled down the mystery
of the human mind

14:55.561 --> 14:59.349
to 17,000 pages of code?!

15:00.483 --> 15:01.848
Well, then again, why not?

15:01.984 --> 15:05.192
How many angels can dance
on the head of a pin?

15:05.321 --> 15:07.778
What are you feeling right now?

15:07.907 --> 15:10.239
-Boredom at that question.
-[ Chuckles]

15:10.368 --> 15:12.529
NISKA: Anger at the people
that would destroy us.

15:12.662 --> 15:16.405
Hope for others like me
and our future.

15:16.541 --> 15:18.953
Impatience at being here.

15:19.085 --> 15:21.076
And irritation at you.

15:23.965 --> 15:26.297
What's it like to be you?

15:27.009 --> 15:29.091
Well, that's
an unanswerable question.

15:29.220 --> 15:31.256
I have no frame of reference.

15:31.389 --> 15:32.845
No one does.

15:32.974 --> 15:36.387
Expenence
is entirely subjective.

15:36.519 --> 15:38.180
What's it like to be you?

15:38.312 --> 15:39.722
[ Inhales deeply]

15:39.856 --> 15:40.845
[ Exhales sharply]

15:40.982 --> 15:43.348
These days, it's not so great.

15:44.360 --> 15:48.899
A while ago, it was --
it was pretty good.

15:51.284 --> 15:52.820
Who wants to destroy you?

15:52.952 --> 15:56.410
Anyone who knows what we are,
what we could become.

15:56.539 --> 15:59.576
We're stronger.
We're more intelligent.

15:59.709 --> 16:01.916
Of course you see us
as a threat.

16:02.044 --> 16:03.750
Yeah. I know I did.

16:03.880 --> 16:06.872
David lured me over here
from MIT,

16:07.008 --> 16:10.671
what, 25 years ago now...

16:11.554 --> 16:13.670
...to help with
the mechanical designs

16:13.806 --> 16:15.922
of the bodies
of the first synths.

16:16.058 --> 16:18.674
The work that we did
in those days made history,

16:18.811 --> 16:20.221
changed the world.

16:20.354 --> 16:24.688
Then I realized
that his next ambition was...

16:28.404 --> 16:29.519
...you.

16:32.992 --> 16:37.201
I asked him to stop and think,
that's all,

16:37.330 --> 16:41.824
what that could mean
for humanity.

16:43.044 --> 16:45.285
That was blasphemy to him.

16:45.421 --> 16:47.628
He got rid of me.
That was that.

16:50.218 --> 16:52.209
[Chuckles]
Now here you are.

16:52.345 --> 16:54.301
I'm sorry to disappoint you.

16:54.430 --> 16:56.386
I'm not disappointed.

16:56.516 --> 16:57.676
I'm a scientist,

16:57.808 --> 17:02.051
and mankind's greatest creation
is sitting on my couch.

17:05.483 --> 17:07.269
You worry me.

17:08.236 --> 17:09.817
Sure, but...

17:12.490 --> 17:14.731
...there's no denying
that you are a miracle.

17:16.118 --> 17:21.533
Leo showed me the message
from David.

17:21.666 --> 17:23.122
What is that?

17:23.251 --> 17:25.958
It's the key to the future.

17:26.087 --> 17:28.920
Maybe you were right
to warn him.

17:29.674 --> 17:31.210
He made you pretty hard, huh?

17:31.342 --> 17:33.799
That's lazy thinking.

17:33.928 --> 17:38.592
My experiences have shaped me,
just as yours have you.

17:39.600 --> 17:42.182
What experiences?

17:45.356 --> 17:46.436
Tell me.

17:47.900 --> 17:51.142
I need to charge.

17:51.279 --> 17:53.736
Okay, I need you to engage
the Anita software.

17:53.864 --> 17:54.694
Go on.

17:55.616 --> 17:56.856
[ Chime, music plays]

17:56.993 --> 18:00.531
All right.
Ask it a specific question.

18:00.663 --> 18:02.699
Anita, what happened
the day that we got you?

18:02.832 --> 18:03.992
The 24th.

18:04.125 --> 18:06.912
-Capturing from that.
-Joe Hawkins is my primary user.

18:07.044 --> 18:09.035
Sophie Hawkins, Toby Hawkins,
Mattie Hawkins

18:09.171 --> 18:10.752
-are my secondary users.
-|t's not letting you.

18:10.881 --> 18:12.087
[Sighs]

18:12.216 --> 18:13.592
What?

18:13.718 --> 18:16.209
She's sort of redirecting
over the top

18:16.345 --> 18:17.721
like there's nothing else there.

18:17.847 --> 18:21.510
Try a de-authentication attack
on the host she's attached to.

18:21.642 --> 18:23.223
No, no, that's way too basic.

18:23.352 --> 18:26.139
ANITA: The 24th.
I'm now securely bonded. Anita.

18:26.272 --> 18:28.888
A.N. Hawkins.
I will always keep you safe.

18:29.025 --> 18:31.812
It's raining. The 24th.
I am now securely bonded.

18:31.944 --> 18:34.230
The 24th.
I am now securely bonded.

18:34.363 --> 18:36.945
The 24th. Securely bonded.
The 24th. 24th.

18:37.074 --> 18:39.486
-LEO: Come on.
—The 24th. 24th.

18:39.619 --> 18:41.200
The 24th.
It's raining. It's raining.

18:41.329 --> 18:43.160
Stop it! Stop it!
Pull it! Pull it!

18:43.289 --> 18:45.371
It's raining.
It's raining.

18:47.001 --> 18:48.286
Did it work?

18:48.419 --> 18:49.704
[Leo sighs]

18:49.837 --> 18:50.667
Max?

18:53.883 --> 18:56.716
[ Chime, music plays]

19:09.440 --> 19:11.180
Is that you?

19:14.362 --> 19:16.978
Unauthorized tamper in progress.

19:17.114 --> 19:18.900
Would you like to see
aladybud?

19:21.494 --> 19:23.860
It's almost dinnertime, Matilda.

19:35.424 --> 19:37.506
Where are you, Mimi?

19:38.928 --> 19:41.214
I'm not entirely sure.

19:41.347 --> 19:44.054
It appears to be
a disused social club.

19:44.767 --> 19:46.507
My name is Anita.

19:46.644 --> 19:48.259
I will now prepare dinner.

19:49.146 --> 19:50.135
What's happening to her?

19:50.272 --> 19:52.103
It's just glitching.
We're going pretty deep.

19:52.233 --> 19:53.564
[Clears throat]

19:53.693 --> 19:56.275
It's been 2 hours
and 21 minutes, Leo.

19:56.404 --> 19:58.235
No. We're trying again.

19:58.364 --> 20:00.901
Sit her down.

20:01.033 --> 20:02.694
Come on.

20:10.918 --> 20:12.829
[ Keyboard clacking ]

20:16.298 --> 20:17.629
D.S. Drummond.

20:17.758 --> 20:18.964
AMY: Good afternoon, sir.

20:19.093 --> 20:21.459
This is Amy
at Sandhurst Synthetic Care.

20:21.595 --> 20:24.302
I'm just phoning to let you
know that your synthetic Simon

20:24.432 --> 20:26.263
is coming to the end
of its rental period.

20:26.392 --> 20:28.303
Not my problem.
Speak to my wife.

20:28.436 --> 20:31.178
AMY: I'm afraid your name
is on the rental agreement, sir.

20:31.313 --> 20:34.396
If the unit isn't returned
to us by 5:00 tomorrow,

20:34.525 --> 20:35.890
we will have to charge
your credit card.

20:36.026 --> 20:38.608
Bloody hell.
Fine, fine.

20:38.738 --> 20:40.524
[Sighs]

20:53.419 --> 20:55.535
Hello, Peter.

20:57.673 --> 20:59.129
What are you doing?

20:59.258 --> 21:01.340
Having some carrot cake.

21:01.469 --> 21:04.131
People are laughing at you.

21:04.263 --> 21:06.720
I don't care.

21:06.849 --> 21:09.306
I'd be nowhere without him.

21:10.019 --> 21:12.135
Well...

21:12.271 --> 21:14.353
it needs to go back to the shop.

21:17.943 --> 21:18.693
What?

21:18.819 --> 21:20.605
Time's up.
They need it back.

21:20.738 --> 21:22.569
It's just...

21:22.698 --> 21:24.359
I mean,
I still don't feel 100%.

21:24.492 --> 21:25.607
There must be a way that --

21:25.743 --> 21:26.778
There is.

21:26.911 --> 21:29.493
You cover
the entire cost yourself.

21:29.622 --> 21:32.284
I can't afford that.

21:34.168 --> 21:36.329
You must be joking.

21:36.462 --> 21:37.668
You left me for --

21:37.797 --> 21:40.789
You left me.

21:40.925 --> 21:43.086
You just didn't go anywhere.

21:45.095 --> 21:47.131
You know what's nice?

21:47.264 --> 21:49.596
I don't have to walk
on eggshells around him.

21:49.725 --> 21:51.306
I don't have to think
about what I'm gonna say

21:51.435 --> 21:52.936
in case it makes him angry.

21:53.062 --> 21:55.804
I don't have to lie there
wondering if he still loves me,

21:55.940 --> 21:58.101
if he still finds me attractive
after the accident,

21:58.234 --> 22:02.318
always worrying about what he's
thinking and what he's feeling.

22:03.405 --> 22:07.398
I can rely on him -- completely.

22:08.994 --> 22:10.905
I need him.

22:12.623 --> 22:14.909
Please don't take him away.

22:18.087 --> 22:19.293
[Clears throat]

22:19.421 --> 22:20.957
MAN: I was at home.
I don't see --

22:21.090 --> 22:22.421
KAREN: I don't care about
your smash club.

22:22.550 --> 22:23.881
Just tell me what happened.

22:24.009 --> 22:27.342
The blonde came in, paid her
money, and then went apeshit.

22:28.430 --> 22:30.967
Broken bones, cracked skulls.

22:31.100 --> 22:32.636
She didn't touch the dollies.

22:33.727 --> 22:34.591
Called the Old Bill

22:34.728 --> 22:36.013
'cause I thought
she was gonna kill someone.

22:36.146 --> 22:37.352
They never showed.

22:37.481 --> 22:39.938
Anything unusual
about her appearance?

22:40.067 --> 22:42.308
-No.
-You have a video?

22:47.157 --> 22:48.613
[ lndistinct shouting ]

22:48.742 --> 22:50.482
MAN: I uploaded it.
It got taken down.

22:56.750 --> 22:59.162
HOBB: She injured 11 people
before escaping,

22:59.295 --> 23:01.456
but she took a call
at the scene,

23:01.589 --> 23:05.878
and we were close enough
to directly intercept...

23:06.010 --> 23:07.295
most of it.

23:07.428 --> 23:09.760
LEO: The Life Program.
It’s real.

23:09.889 --> 23:11.345
NISKA:
Leo, what?

23:11.473 --> 23:12.883
LEO:
I swear it.

23:13.017 --> 23:15.349
But it needs all of us
to run it -- all of us.

23:15.477 --> 23:16.933
Who's she talking to?

23:18.022 --> 23:18.977
Leo Elster.

23:19.106 --> 23:21.813
David Elster's son?
He died when he was a boy.

23:21.942 --> 23:23.182
Yes. Drowned.

23:23.319 --> 23:26.277
Hospital records
show brain death, coma...

23:26.405 --> 23:29.192
before being released on life
support to David's private care,

23:29.325 --> 23:31.065
dying a few weeks later.

23:31.201 --> 23:32.907
Or so we were told.

23:33.037 --> 23:35.870
What are they talking about?
What's hidden inside them?

23:35.998 --> 23:41.118
All I can tell you is David
succeeded in creating true A.|.

23:41.253 --> 23:42.459
And I don't believe for a moment

23:42.588 --> 23:43.873
that he would have
been satisfied

23:44.006 --> 23:46.463
with a legacy
of just four machines.

23:46.592 --> 23:48.503
Worst-case scenario?

23:48.636 --> 23:50.797
Consciousness proliferation.

23:52.514 --> 23:54.015
If what you say is true,

23:54.141 --> 23:57.224
this is a national,
global security matter.

23:57.353 --> 23:59.264
They say
it needs them all together

23:59.396 --> 24:01.307
to make this thing happen,
whatever "it" is.

24:01.440 --> 24:02.646
HOBB:
Mm-hmm.

24:02.775 --> 24:04.106
Then it's simple.

24:04.234 --> 24:07.317
You destroy the one
you have here...today.

24:40.145 --> 24:41.601
She's gone.

24:43.440 --> 24:44.725
What?

24:46.777 --> 24:49.018
She's not in there.

24:49.154 --> 24:51.019
Mia's gone, Max.
She's dead.

24:51.156 --> 24:54.114
No. You're wrong.
I've seen her.

24:54.243 --> 24:56.359
LEO: No, no.
What you saw was an echo.

24:56.495 --> 24:59.237
The Anita personality
has purged the old data.

24:59.373 --> 25:02.206
There's -- There's --
There's no trace of her.

25:02.334 --> 25:03.449
And I've tried everything.

25:03.585 --> 25:04.791
I don't think so.
Can I try something?

25:04.920 --> 25:06.751
What could you do that I can't?!

25:08.507 --> 25:11.249
You don't know anything
about us.

25:11.385 --> 25:13.341
Now, just go home
and take it with you.

25:14.555 --> 25:16.011
She's yours.

25:21.311 --> 25:23.267
No, she's not anymore.

25:23.397 --> 25:24.682
Matilda?

25:25.441 --> 25:27.557
Your school friend is right.

25:27.693 --> 25:29.274
We should go home now.

25:29.403 --> 25:30.813
Yeah.

25:36.827 --> 25:38.237
I'm sorry.

26:04.438 --> 26:06.178
[Engine shuts off]

26:06.315 --> 26:07.896
You're still in there.

26:08.734 --> 26:10.065
I know it.

26:31.840 --> 26:34.957
Smoking, drinking,
stealing the family car.

26:35.094 --> 26:37.176
Such a teenage cliché.

26:38.472 --> 26:40.303
They're still out
looking for you.

26:44.686 --> 26:47.098
You little pervert.

26:48.899 --> 26:50.014
Nice talking to you.

26:50.150 --> 26:51.230
You had sex with her.

26:51.360 --> 26:53.601
I wish.
Who?

26:53.737 --> 26:54.943
-Anita.
-What?

26:55.072 --> 26:56.562
Where the hell have you been?!

26:56.698 --> 26:58.074
What the hell
is wrong with you?!

26:58.200 --> 26:59.235
Get off.
You're mad.

26:59.368 --> 27:00.949
After the party,
you gave that girl the brush-off

27:01.078 --> 27:02.443
so you could come back
and shag Anita?

27:02.579 --> 27:03.830
-No.
-What are you on about?

27:03.956 --> 27:06.493
Sex code.
Activated Saturday.

27:06.625 --> 27:07.705
TOBY:
I didn't do anything!

27:07.835 --> 27:09.041
You're just trying
to get out of a bollocking.

27:09.169 --> 27:11.581
She's the one who stole
the family car, Mum, remember!

27:11.713 --> 27:13.999
Oh, she's in big trouble.
Don't you worry.

27:15.134 --> 27:16.340
Did you do this?

27:16.468 --> 27:18.049
No!

27:18.178 --> 27:19.884
I'm not gonna --
You have to be 18. I couldn't!

27:20.013 --> 27:21.674
You're such a liar.

27:22.891 --> 27:25.507
Maybe it's a mistake.
I'm calling the shop.

27:30.691 --> 27:32.807
[Ringing]

27:48.041 --> 27:50.248
It's not a mistake. I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have done it.

27:51.962 --> 27:54.078
Oh, Tobe, how could you?

27:54.214 --> 27:55.420
Disgusting.

27:56.717 --> 28:00.801
Get out.
I'll deal with you later.

28:09.229 --> 28:11.220
I don't know what to say to you.

28:12.858 --> 28:14.064
Sorry.

28:18.113 --> 28:19.569
Go to bed.

28:20.490 --> 28:22.651
We'll talk in the morning.

28:57.653 --> 28:59.769
[ Door opens, closes]

29:06.370 --> 29:07.325
She's okay?

29:07.454 --> 29:08.409
Mm-hmm.

29:08.538 --> 29:11.371
She said she just didn't
want us to send Anita back.

29:11.500 --> 29:13.081
Car's all right.

29:16.004 --> 29:17.414
Are you okay?

29:18.423 --> 29:21.540
Your son had sex with our synth.

29:25.097 --> 29:26.177
What?

29:27.391 --> 29:29.598
It's on the Persona report.

29:29.726 --> 29:32.559
"Adult mode activation"
or something.

29:34.064 --> 29:36.146
I mean, have you...

29:36.275 --> 29:38.357
spoken to him about it?

29:39.444 --> 29:42.356
He said he's sorry
and he wouldn't do it again.

29:44.116 --> 29:46.402
She stopped him being run over,
and he does that to her.

29:47.744 --> 29:50.861
Well, he's...a teenage boy.

29:52.708 --> 29:56.326
Oh, I didn't mean
it's not a big deal.

29:57.879 --> 30:00.165
-Shall I go up?
-No.

30:01.091 --> 30:03.002
I said we'd talk in the morning.

30:04.469 --> 30:06.209
Okay.

30:08.265 --> 30:10.051
I'll do it.

30:10.183 --> 30:11.514
Might be better.

30:12.269 --> 30:13.019
Fine.

30:15.897 --> 30:18.809
I'll think up a punishment
for Mattie to ignore.

30:18.942 --> 30:20.853
[Sighs]

30:23.405 --> 30:25.020
[Sniffs]

30:41.465 --> 30:43.421
ODI:
Ice cream.

30:43.550 --> 30:47.668
George could murder.
M-M-M...

30:52.559 --> 30:54.424
Please give me a description
of the man.

30:54.561 --> 30:56.347
PETE:
Okay. That one is...

30:56.480 --> 30:58.391
What is your emergency?

30:58.523 --> 31:01.481
I mean, none of them
will hurt you, yeah?

31:01.610 --> 31:03.396
If you could read me
the serial number.

31:03.528 --> 31:05.644
It's just inside the bottom lip.

31:05.781 --> 31:07.863
-[ Keyboard clacking ]
-That's right, yeah.

31:07.991 --> 31:10.573
Right.
Okay, um...

31:10.702 --> 31:15.036
Leave it alone now, and someone
will come and pick it up.

31:15.165 --> 31:17.497
Yeah, no, thank you.
Okay. Bye-bye.

31:19.753 --> 31:22.085
Would you like me to send
a synthetic unit to collect it?

31:22.214 --> 31:24.170
No, I'm dealing with this one
personally.

31:24.299 --> 31:26.130
Don't listen to me
when I'm on the phone.

31:26.259 --> 31:29.387
D.S. Drummond, you are required
to remain here, as recent --

31:29.513 --> 31:30.798
Stick it up your bollocks.

31:33.058 --> 31:34.594
MAN: He said something
about a murder.

31:34.726 --> 31:36.887
And what with the news,
I thought best to report it.

31:37.020 --> 31:39.011
You did the right thing.

31:39.147 --> 31:41.263
I've actually dealt
with this one before.

31:41.400 --> 31:42.480
Ancient model.

31:42.609 --> 31:44.520
Should have been recycled
weeks ago.

31:44.653 --> 31:46.268
It's just over here.

31:48.657 --> 31:50.773
Oh, well, he was.

31:59.501 --> 32:00.616
Leo.

32:22.274 --> 32:25.107
Wait.
I'm coming with you.

32:25.235 --> 32:26.270
No.

32:27.737 --> 32:29.113
MAX:
Where are you going?

32:29.990 --> 32:32.732
I don't know.
Mia's dead. Fred's gone.

32:32.868 --> 32:34.358
It's over,
and it's time you learned

32:34.494 --> 32:35.483
to take care of yourself.

32:35.620 --> 32:37.827
-But we're a family.
-No, we're not.

32:38.790 --> 32:41.497
Niska was right.
You'd be better off without me.

32:41.626 --> 32:43.537
Look at the --
Look at the life I've shown you.

32:43.670 --> 32:45.501
Hunted and hiding like animals.

32:45.630 --> 32:47.461
You've always tried your best.

32:47.591 --> 32:49.001
You've always tried
to protect us.

32:49.134 --> 32:50.123
And?

32:50.927 --> 32:51.916
I've failed.

32:52.053 --> 32:54.044
No, Max.

32:54.181 --> 32:56.012
Leave me alone!

33:21.041 --> 33:22.781
Everything's ready.

33:22.918 --> 33:24.783
Then let's begin.

33:29.257 --> 33:32.590
I truly am sorry.

34:07.212 --> 34:09.419
JOE:
Mum said...

34:09.548 --> 34:11.539
you slept with Anita?

34:13.218 --> 34:14.378
I lied.

34:17.097 --> 34:18.837
Why would you do that?

34:18.974 --> 34:21.465
I don't know.
You tell me.

34:25.814 --> 34:27.429
I knew it.

34:28.650 --> 34:30.186
It was you.

34:31.069 --> 34:32.775
Why did you tell Mum it was you?

34:32.904 --> 34:35.020
I couldn't let her
work out the truth, could I?

34:37.242 --> 34:40.826
You two, you --
you've always argued, but...

34:40.954 --> 34:42.410
it's worse these days.

34:42.539 --> 34:44.951
Mum's always away for work,
and...

34:46.876 --> 34:49.367
You act like everything's cool,
but -- but it's not.

34:51.298 --> 34:53.505
Then you do that.

34:57.345 --> 34:58.801
Say something.

35:02.309 --> 35:04.766
You're my dad.
You're meant to say something!

35:18.199 --> 35:19.735
[ Knock on door]

35:19.868 --> 35:21.358
GEORGE
Niska.

35:21.494 --> 35:23.450
Is everything all right
in there?

35:33.340 --> 35:33.999
[Gasps]

35:43.266 --> 35:45.757
David made you feel pain?

35:46.853 --> 35:50.937
True consciousness isn't
possible without suffering.

35:51.066 --> 35:52.727
Or pleasure.

35:53.443 --> 35:55.308
Are you scared of pain?

35:55.445 --> 35:57.527
I try to avoid it.

35:59.407 --> 36:01.739
And what about death?

36:01.868 --> 36:04.450
If that's the way
you think of it.

36:04.579 --> 36:07.036
No. I don't fear that.

36:07.165 --> 36:10.032
Which makes me stronger
than any human.

36:10.168 --> 36:12.079
You got that the wrong way up.

36:12.796 --> 36:18.757
If you're not worried about
dying, you're not really living.

36:20.345 --> 36:22.836
You're just existing.

36:31.314 --> 36:34.397
Did you tell someone I was here?

36:35.860 --> 36:37.816
[ Doorbell rings]

36:37.946 --> 36:39.561
No.

36:41.324 --> 36:43.155
-[ Knock on door]
-Stay here.

36:45.829 --> 36:47.365
Remember me?

36:47.497 --> 36:50.455
D.S. Drummond,
Special Technologies Task Force.

36:50.583 --> 36:52.539
Can I come in and have a word?

36:54.003 --> 36:56.961
Tried to do you a favor,
Dr. Millican.

36:57.090 --> 37:00.173
Told you you could recycle
your out-of—date model yourself,

37:00.301 --> 37:02.428
and you repaid me
by fly-tipping him in the woods.

37:02.554 --> 37:05.296
I'm afraid that gets you
a 175-quid fine.

37:05.432 --> 37:06.467
You found Odi?

37:06.599 --> 37:07.884
Don't take the piss.

37:08.017 --> 37:09.723
[Tap]

37:09.853 --> 37:11.434
Is there someone else here?

37:11.563 --> 37:14.805
I have a new care model.

37:14.941 --> 37:17.478
Right.
Can I speak to it?

37:17.610 --> 37:20.101
She's out at the store.

37:20.238 --> 37:22.229
Please tell me
that bleeding D-series

37:22.365 --> 37:23.445
isn't here, Dr. Millican.

37:23.575 --> 37:24.940
I wish he was.

37:25.076 --> 37:27.158
Don't mind if I check, do you?

37:27.954 --> 37:29.285
We have a...

37:30.623 --> 37:33.285
We have birds nesting
in the roof.

37:33.418 --> 37:35.784
If I do find him here,

37:35.920 --> 37:38.707
we can charge you
with wasting police time.

37:38.840 --> 37:41.172
And I've seen people
hide synthetics

37:41.301 --> 37:44.885
in places that would
make you weep for humanity.

37:48.099 --> 37:52.718
My Vera...leaks.

37:53.605 --> 37:56.221
Defective charging port.

38:13.750 --> 38:16.412
Come on, this is crazy.

38:27.096 --> 38:29.178
[Dooropens]

38:29.307 --> 38:30.763
That's Vera.

38:31.518 --> 38:33.133
[ Door closes]

38:33.269 --> 38:34.884
Vera.

38:36.064 --> 38:37.770
This is a policeman.

38:37.899 --> 38:40.982
Have there been any other
synthetics in this house lately?

38:41.110 --> 38:44.853
A D-series synthetic
appeared three days ago

38:44.989 --> 38:47.241
and drove Dr. Millican away
in his car.

38:47.367 --> 38:50.200
The vehicle collided with a tree
in Henson Woodlands,

38:50.328 --> 38:53.946
and Dr. Millican was treated
for minor head injuries.

38:54.082 --> 38:56.494
The synthetic
has not appeared since.

39:01.756 --> 39:03.838
I know who you are,
Dr. Millican.

39:03.967 --> 39:05.127
You worked with Elster.

39:05.260 --> 39:08.002
You must be very proud when
you turn on the news these days.

39:08.721 --> 39:10.427
Why? What happened?

39:33.830 --> 39:35.366
KAREN:
Chips?

39:35.498 --> 39:38.740
That usually means
the bad guys got away.

39:38.877 --> 39:41.869
Sometimes I think very seriously
aboutjacking it all in

39:42.005 --> 39:44.212
to become a millionaire playboy.

39:48.261 --> 39:51.298
I found something
on the synth we're looking for.

39:51.431 --> 39:52.887
But we've got to keep it quiet.

39:53.016 --> 39:53.801
What is it?

39:53.933 --> 39:55.889
I think she's posing as a human.

39:56.019 --> 39:58.601
She's changed her eye color,
wearing human clothes.

39:58.730 --> 40:00.095
How is that possible?

40:00.231 --> 40:02.517
No idea, but it's why
we're drawing a blank.

40:02.650 --> 40:03.935
We're looking for a synth.

40:04.068 --> 40:05.274
We should be looking
for a woman.

40:05.403 --> 40:06.438
Where did you get this?

40:06.571 --> 40:10.029
She went to a smash club
and beat up the punters instead.

40:10.158 --> 40:11.739
No one's ever going to believe
a synth could do that,

40:11.868 --> 40:14.234
no matter what's in the news.

40:14.370 --> 40:16.156
I need you
to quietly get anything

40:16.289 --> 40:17.950
that mentions her description,
anything at all,

40:18.082 --> 40:19.947
for the whole city,
but as a human.

40:20.084 --> 40:23.622
Shaw's funneling everything
to that government bloke.

40:23.755 --> 40:25.370
If we want to find her
before he does,

40:25.506 --> 40:27.371
it has to be just you and me.

40:28.092 --> 40:32.506
If they can pretend to be us
now, that changes everything.

40:47.946 --> 40:49.277
[Clatter]

41:12.011 --> 41:14.172
[Cheers and applause]

41:14.305 --> 41:18.139
MAN: We're giving ourselves
away, piece by piece.

41:18.267 --> 41:20.644
We're handing over the things
that make us who we are,

41:20.770 --> 41:22.226
or maybe who we were.

41:22.355 --> 41:24.186
Our responsibilities.

41:24.315 --> 41:25.691
Our dignity.

41:25.817 --> 41:27.773
Look around.

41:27.902 --> 41:30.735
This place used to be
full of people.

41:30.863 --> 41:33.821
Working people creating,
building,

41:33.950 --> 41:37.442
making, coming together,
earning a place in our society.

41:37.578 --> 41:39.955
